dct_description_sm: California as an island with flat northern coast and no place names. Land of Jesso and S. of Vries to northwest, and S. of Annian to north. Western Canada is called New North Wales.Prime Meridian: [Tenerife].
Reissued in: The compleat geographer ... , [page] 473 / by Herman Moll, [170?].

At page top, above map: A General and Particular Description of AMERICA., with AMERICA printed over the title of the map. [page] 473 (top right). CHAP I. Of America in General (bottom middle printed over bottom of the map).
